RIYADH: Saudi Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs Waleed bin Abdulkarim Al-Khuraiji on Sunday met Ambassador of Algeria to the Kingdom Mohammed Ali Boughazi.
During the reception at the ministry’s headquarters in Riyadh, the two reviewed bilateral relations and ways to enhance them in all fields.
They also discussed the most prominent regional and international developments of common interest.
Earlier, Saudi Minister of State for Foreign Affairs Adel Al-Jubeir received the Algerian envoy in Riyadh and wished him success in his new duties.